				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">2 methods...<br /><br />1. have 2 separate arrays for each flip state (faster to draw, but takes up more bytes of ROM) that already has the H flip bit set.<br /><br />or<br /><br />2. subtract each x coordinate from a central x point (slower, but needs 1/2 the ROM space)...and also set the H flip bit for each sprite.<br /><br />central x - relative x = flipped x.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

